
# Topic 3: Databricks vs Apache Spark vs EMR vs Synapse

## Concept

These are different technologies used for big data processing. **Apache Spark** is the processing engine, while **Databricks, EMR, and Synapse** are platforms/services that use Spark.

---

## Theory

| Technology   | Purpose                                                   |
| ------------ | --------------------------------------------------------- |
| Apache Spark | Distributed data processing engine                        |
| Databricks   | Managed Lakehouse platform built on Spark                 |
| EMR          | AWS-managed big data platform (Spark, Hive, Hadoop, etc.) |
| Synapse      | Azure analytics platform (SQL + Spark + Data Warehouse)   |

---

## Architecture

```text
Apache Spark
      │
      ├── Databricks (AWS/Azure/GCP)
      ├── AWS EMR
      └── Azure Synapse
```

> Spark is the engine. The others provide infrastructure and management around it.

---

## Syntax

**Spark (same everywhere)**

```python
df = spark.read.csv("/path/file.csv", header=True)
```

The Spark code is nearly identical on Databricks, EMR, and Synapse.

